<statement>
<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/mom-1057110-1.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 3 and b = 8. Calculate:</p>
<p>
c = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 3" class="text"/></p>
<p>
A = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1001" id="qn1001" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 2 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1002" id="qn1002" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 3 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>8.5</li><li>20.6</li><li>69.4</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={3}^{{2}}+{8}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={9}+{64}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={73}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{73}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{8.5440037453175}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{8.5}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arctan{{\left(\frac{{3}}{{8}}\right)}}}\approx{20.556045219583}\approx{20.6}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{20.556045219583}^{\circ}\approx{69.443954780417}\approx{69.4}</m>.</p>

</solution>
